                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51 Public Works Debt/151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-02T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 2, 1938—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 2—1:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>132. Montoulieu yesterday confirmed in writing to Mr. Crafts the general
                    agreement outlined in the Embassy’s telegram No. 130, November 1, 1 p.m. Mr.
                    Crafts in a letter to the Cuban Ambassador yesterday likewise confirmed general
                    agreement subject to working out of details. Cuban Ambassador told Mr. Crafts
                    last night the President had approved agreement. Montoulieu and Gorrin<note
                        n="37" xml:id="d496fn37">Attorney for the Chase National Bank.</note> are
                    working out details of new taxes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
